TASK:

You are given the dataset phones-v1.csv, which contains information about mobile phones (brand, model, display, battery capacity, OS, memory, CPU, release year, and more).
Your goal is to perform a complete data preprocessing and machine learning workflow to build a model that predicts the price category of a phone:
low price
medium price
high price

Requirements:
1) Load and Initial Analysis

Load the dataset using pandas.read_csv().

Display the first rows (head()), descriptive statistics (describe()), class distribution (value_counts()), and a correlation matrix.

Create basic visualizations (histograms, heatmap, pairplot, etc.).

2) Cleaning and Transforming Categorical Columns

Encode the categorical columns:

Brand → one-hot encoding

Display Type → one-hot encoding

OS → one-hot encoding

Remove the Model column (too many unique values, low predictive value).

Remove the Launch column (string date format, not used in the model).

3) Processing the “Dimensions” Column

The dimensions are provided as text in the format:
"143.6 x 70.9 x 7.7 mm"

Extract:

Height

Width

Thickness

Create three new numeric columns and remove the original Dimensions column.

4) Additional Cleaning Steps

Convert NFC from boolean to integer (True → 1, False → 0).

Map the values in CPU to the number of cores:

Quad-Core → 4

Hexa-Core → 6

Octa-Core → 8

5) Encoding the Target Variable

Encode Price Range using OrdinalEncoder with the following order:

low price → 0

medium price → 1

high price → 2

6) Handling Missing Values

Use Iterative Imputer to fill missing values for the following columns:

Battery (mAh)

Display Size

CPU

Apple

Height

Thickness

OLED

Android

iOS

7) Splitting the Dataset

Split the dataset into training and testing sets using an 80/20 ratio.

8) Feature Scaling

Normalize the feature values using MinMaxScaler (range: 0 to 1).

9) Train Three Machine-Learning Models

Train and evaluate the following classifiers:

Logistic Regression

K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

Decision Tree

For each model, display the classification report.

10) Model Tuning with GridSearchCV

Perform hyperparameter tuning for the Decision Tree using:

criterion ∈ {gini, entropy}

max_depth ∈ {None, 1, 2, 3, 4}

Display the best parameters and generate predictions using the best estimator.
